div.p:
Wherefore, I the Lord, knowing the calamity which should come upon the inhabitants of the
earth, called upon my servant Joseph Smith, Jun., and spake unto him from heaven, and gave
him commandments;

But that every man might speak in the name of God the Lord, even the Savior of the world;
That faith also might increase in the earth;
That mine everlasting covenant might be established;
That the fulness of my gospel might be proclaimed by the weak and the simple unto the ends
of the world, and before kings and rulers
(D&C 1:17-23).

And verily I say unto you, that they who go forth, bearing these tidings unto the inhabitants
of the earth, to them is power given to seal both on earth and in heaven, the unbelieving and
rebellious;
